      • myAttribute

        public myAttribute(java.lang.String newname,
                   int type,
                   boolean newinput)
        Creates an attribute with the name of the attribute, the data type of the attribute and whether the attribute is input or output; the rest of the values are initialized with empty values that we can identify. It is used when we create a nominal attribute.
        Parameters:
        newname - The name of the attribute that is going to be created
        type - The data type of the attribute that is going to be created
        newinput - Whereas the attribute that is going to be created is input or output

      • myAttribute

        public myAttribute(java.lang.String newname,
                   int type,
                   double newmin,
                   double newmax,
                   boolean newinput)
        Creates an attribute with the name of the attribute, the data type of the attribute, the minimum value for the attribute, the maximum value for the attribute, the minimum value for the attribute and whether the attribute is input or output; the rest of the values arte initialized with empty values that we can identify. It is used when we create a numerical attribute.
        Parameters:
        newname - The name of the attribute that is going to be created
        type - The data type of the attribute that is going to be created
        newmin - The minimum value for the attribute that is going to be created
        newmax - The maximum value for the attribute that is going to be created
        newinput - Whereas the attribute that is going to be created is input or output
